<subSubSection id="FFD2654BFF9DFF874CD41C605BD7B00F" pageId="8" pageNumber="573" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B77736C0FF9DFF874CD41C605BD7B00F" blockId="8.[151,1436,1853,1916]" pageId="8" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis id="85BCEAD2FF9DFF874CD41C605E6EB024" bold="true" box="[151,256,1853,1879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="573">Remark.</emphasis>
As explained in the Introduction, the morphology of this species is consistent with the two species of 
<taxonomicName id="70C84D43FF9DFF874CD41C3C5E5CB008" authorityName="Chamberlin &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="1935" box="[151,306,1889,1915]" class="Arachnida" family="Phrurolithidae" genus="Phrurotimpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="85BCEAD2FF9DFF874CD41C3C5E5CB008" box="[151,306,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="573">Phrurotimpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described in this paper, and we therefore transfer this species to the latter genus.
</paragraph>
